        "name": "Code verification via method of manufactured solutions and benchmark comparisons",
        "description": "Observed order of accuracy must be within 10% of formal order for all governing equation residuals; benchmark results must fall within published reference corridors for the FDA nozzle and backward-facing step cases."
      },
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions confirms second-order spatial accuracy (observed p = 1.94). ASME V&V 20 benchmark suite results for the FDA nozzle are within ±2% of the published reference solution corridor. Code verification is fully documented in Appendix B of the evidence dossier."
